# Wireless Infrastructure

To make the lab more representative of a real office environment, an Access Point was deployed between the administrator workstation and the wired network infrastructure.

The administrator workstation connected to the wireless network and obtained connectivity to the router and switch through the access layer.

This allowed SSH management traffic to traverse the wireless network before reaching the infrastructure devices.

Benefits demonstrated:

- Wireless administrative access
- Enterprise network accessibility
- Infrastructure management without physical connections
- Integration of wired and wireless network segments

