# Real-World Relevance

This lab demonstrates how network administrators securely manage infrastructure devices from their workstation without requiring direct physical access.

In many office environments, administrators connect through corporate wired or wireless networks and remotely access routers, switches, firewalls, and other infrastructure devices using SSH.

The lab also highlights how wireless infrastructure integrates with the wired network to provide secure administrative access to network resources.

While local user accounts were used in this lab, larger organizations typically use centralized authentication systems such as:

- RADIUS
- TACACS+

to manage administrator access across many devices from a single location.
